        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>61, Grosvenor Street | London, W.</placeName>
                    <date>Apr 18. 1870.</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am so sorry I cannot come on Thursday, as I must be back in Leipzig Saturday.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> It is my fault not to have written to you before. But always trying to get on with the work I undertook I looked upon a visit in your house as a sort of premium after toilsome weeks.</p>
<p>I must then ask you to allow me to come and see you in the autumn.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>With the best wishes for your health believe me | Ever yours sincerely, | J. Victor Carus</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7165.xml" resp="#automat">letter from J. V. Carus, 16 April [1870]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Carus did not visit CD in the autumn, being prevented by the Franco-Prussian war (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7332.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from J. V. Carus, 2 October 1870</ref>).</note>
